Replace wrong age values with mean age¶

  • 31 patients out of 565897 have 0 age values
  • 1351 patients out of 565897 have 999 age values
  • (1382/565897)*100 0.24% patients do not have right age values
  • Mean age of patients in this dataset is 38.76.
  • Wrong age values will be replaced with age 39
In [9]:
patient_visit['age'].mean()
patient_visit['age'] = patient_visit.age.replace([0, 999], [39, 39] )

Text(0.5, 1.0, 'Hospital departments with maximim ER delay')
  • Average delay in moving from ER to hospital department is 2.54 days for patients in this dataset
  • Hospital unit 1, Emergency Internal Medicine Unit has the maximum delay of 3.6 days in moving from ER followed by hospital unit 7, Emergency Psychiatry Unit
  • Hospital unit 11, Emergency Maternity Unit has minimum delay of 0.8 days in moving from ER followed by hospital unit 10 Emergency Maternity Unit
  • First wards 44 (Intensive Care Unit), 50 (Interventional (Angioplasty) Cardiology), 106 (Pediatric Oncology and Bone Marrow Transplant Unit), 120 (Department of Pediatric Cardiology) have no delays in moving from ER followed by ward. There were 1,11,3, and 2 patients from these departments
  • First ward 39 (Internal Medicine C) and 62 (Department of General Surgery A) have the maximum delay of 4.3 days in moving from ER followed by ward

above_mean = patient_visit[patient_visit.age >=39]
below_mean = patient_visit[patient_visit.age <39]

above = above_mean.outcome.value_counts(normalize=True).mul(100).rename('Percent').reset_index()
above.rename(columns = {'index':'Outcome'}, inplace =True)
above['Outcome'] = above.Outcome.astype(str)

below = below_mean.outcome.value_counts(normalize=True).mul(100).rename('Percent').reset_index()
below.rename(columns = {'index':'Outcome'}, inplace =True)
below['Outcome'] = below.Outcome.astype(str)
